Copying Files with the Copy Command

You use the Copy command to copy one or more files from one location. 
You can use it to copy files from one directory to another on the local computer or on the mapped 
network drive of another computer. You can also use this command to copy files to devices such as LPT1 or COM1 in binary format. 

The syntax of this command is:
Copy [/d] [/v] [/n] [{/y | /-y}] [/z] [{/a | /b}] Source [{/a | /b}] [+ Source [{/a | /b}] [+ ...]] [Destinati
